# ============================================================================
# .gitignore: Nuxt 4 Monorepo (PNPM Workspace) Starter Template
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This comprehensive .gitignore is designed for multi-package adapters
# utilizing:
#   - Nuxt 4 (with Nuxt Layers / Nitro / Vite)
#   - pnpm (primary package manager)
#   - TypeScript, TailwindCSS, Pinia, Vitest, Storybook, Cypress
#
# It employs double-star (**) recursive patterns [cite: 2] to ensure this root
# file safely ignores generated, secret, or volatile content everywhere, even
# within nested packages[cite: 3].
#
# ORGANISATION NOTES
# ------------------
# Sections are ordered from most global + high-churn artifacts (node_modules,
# env files, logs) to framework/tool-specific and finally to project-manager-specific
# runtime data[cite: 1].
#
# EXCEPTIONS
# ----------
# Example files used for onboarding (e.g. .env.example) are re-included
# using negation rules (`!`)[cite: 4, 5].
#
# CUSTOMISING PER-PACKAGE
# -----------------------
# If a specific package needs to include something normally ignored, add a
# local .gitignore in that package folder with an explicit negation pattern[cite: 6].
# ============================================================================

**/.git

# =============================================
# 1. Package Managers & Dependency Stores
# =============================================

# Node dependency trees (high churn, generated)
**/node_modules/

# pnpm stores / virtual links
**/.pnpm-store/
**/.pnp
**/.pnp.*
**/.pnp.js

# Lockfiles from other package managers (pnpm is canonical)
**/package-lock.json
**/yarn.lock
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
# Removed: .firebase/functions/example/node_modules - Too specific, handled by **/node_modules/

# Package manager debug logs
**/app-monitor
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*

# ---

# =============================================
# 2. Environment & Secrets
# =============================================

# Local environment files (per env/machine)
**/.env
**/.env.*

# SERVICE SECRETS (Do not commit credentials)
**/service-account.json

# EXAMPLES / TEMPLATES (Keep tracked for onboarding [cite: 4])
!**/.env.example

# ---

# =============================================
# 3. System / OS Noise
# =============================================

# Microsoft Windows Specific
**/Thumbs.db            # Windows thumbnail cache

# Apple Mac Specific
**/.AppleDouble         # Apple resource forks (network mounts)
**/.DS_Store            # macOS Finder metadata
**/.Spotlight-V100      # macOS indexing data (external drives)
**/.Trashes             # macOS trash on external vols

# 'Unix-like' OS specific
**/lost+found/          # Linux FS recovery artifacts

# ---

# =============================================
# 4. Temporary & Backup Files
# =============================================

# Generic scratch directories
**/tmp/
**/temp/

# Logs (Catching stray logs, dedicated tool logs are handled in respective sections)
*.log                   # Catch stray root-level logs
**/*.log                # Catch logs anywhere (redundant but defensive)

# Generic temp files
*.tmp                   # Generic temp scratch files
*.bak                   # Editor/backup cruft
*.swp                   # Vim swap
*.swo                   # Vim old swap
*.orig                  # Merge conflict backups (git mergetool)

# Legacy / temporary files (e.g., deleted during refactoring)
# **/*.old # Generalising from nuxt.config.ts [cite: 16]

# ---

# =============================================
# 5. Nuxt / Nitro / Vite Build & Cache Artefacts
# =============================================

# Core Nuxt + build caches
**/.cache/
**/.nuxi/
**/.nuxt/
**/.output/
**/.nitro/
**/.vite/

# Conventional build output (client bundles, libraries)
**/dist/

# Nuxt auto-generated route/page caches
**/.nuxt/routes.json
**/.nuxt/pages.json

# Nuxt DevTools runtime cache/config
.nuxt/devtools/

# Nitro runtime + config
**/nitro.json
**/nitro.config.*
**/*.nitro.*             # Catch misc Nitro build files
**/storage/              # Nitro storage mount (local fs, db adapters, etc.)

# Standalone server builds (targeted rules) [cite: 11]
**/nitro/build/
**/nitro/standalone/
**/standalone/           # Legacy pattern retained

# Specific file exclusions
# Temporary exclude to ensure that private data does not pollute the Git repository[cite: 16].
# nuxt.config.ts

# ---

# =============================================
# 6. Testing, Tooling, QA
# =============================================

# Vitest
**/.vitest/
**/vitest.*.json
coverage/                # Coverage output (Vitest, Jest, etc.)


# =============================================
# 7. Vitepress documentation server
# =============================================
docs/.vitepress/dist
docs/.vitepress/cache


# Local development playgrounds / scratch apps
**/playground/dist/
**/playground/.nuxt/
**/playground/.output/
**/sandbox*/

# Storybook
.storybook/
storybook-static/

# Cypress test runner artefacts
cypress/screenshots/
cypress/videos/

# Powershell Generated Layer Documentation
powershell/output/

# ---

# =============================================
# 8. Backend / Hosting Providers
# =============================================

# Firebase (functions, emulators, CLI)
!.firebase                              # Keep configuration file (from .gitignore)
!.firebaserc                            # Keep configuration file (from .gitignore)
!firebase.json                          # Keep configuration file (from .gitignore)
# Keep generated import scripts (from .gitignore)
!firebase/generated_scripts/importData.cjs
!firebase/generated_scripts/importAuthUsers.cjs
**/firebase-debug.log*
**/firebase/functions/package-lock.json # NPM lock (ignored when pnpm is standard)

# Appwrite emulator
**/apphosting.emulator.yaml

# Netlify build state
**/.netlify/

# Vercel project-manager state
**/.vercel/

# ---

# =============================================
# 9. IDE / Editor Project Metadata
# =============================================

# JetBrains IDEs (WebStorm/IntelliJ/etc.)
.idea/
qodana.yaml                   # JetBrains Qodana CI config (ignore local)

# JetBrains Fleet
.fleet/

# VS Code workspace files
.vscode/

# VS Code Example/Template Files (Keep tracked)
!**/.vscode/settings.json.example
!**/.vscode/extensions.json.example

# ---

# =============================================
# 10. TypeScript, Build Info & Transpiled Outputs
# =============================================

**/out-tsc/                  # tsc output (Angular-style or tooling builds)
**/*.tsbuildinfo             # Incremental TS build state

# ---

# =============================================
# 11. Project-Specific Runtime & Dev Data
# =============================================

# Generated data/datasets, exported API pulls, etc.
**/.data/                    # Hidden data scratch
**/.development/             # Hidden variant
**/data/
**/development/              # Local development scratch trees
**/sandbox*/                 # Local scratch (dup with Testing block ok for safety)
# **/backend-mock-data-stores/  # Local backend data mockup.

# ============================================================================
# End of File
